{"word":"στησίχορος","slug":"στησίχορος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n96755\" key=\"sthsi/xoros\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"suff\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">στησί-χορος</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ον</itype>, <sense id=\"n96755.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">establishing</tr_> or <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">leading</tr_> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">χοροί</foreign>:—hence as pr. n., <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Στησίχορος</orth>, <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Dor.\">Dor.</a></gram> </gramGrp> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Στᾱσ-</orth>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ὁ</gen>, the Lyric poet <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Stesichorus\">Stesichorus</a></title_>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0261.tlg001:53\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Simon.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">53</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0059.tlg012:243a\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pl.\">Pl.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Phdr.\">Phdr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">243a</biblScope> </bibl>: prov., <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">οὐδὲ τὰ τρία Στησιχόρου</foreign> (i.e. strophe, antistrophos, epode) <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">γνῶναι</foreign>, of illiterate persons, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0097.tlg001:7:14\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Diogenian.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">7.14</biblScope> </bibl>:—<pos opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"pos\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Adj.\